### 3.5 PCA9685 PWM Driver (I2C — 16-channel Servo Driver)

| Ref | Qty | Component | Value/Part | Package | Description |
|-----|-----|-----------|------------|---------|-------------|
| J6 | 1 | Female Pin Header | 1×6 pins, 2.54mm | Through-hole | PCA9685 module control header |
| R11 | 1 | Resistor | 4.7kΩ | 0603 | I2C SDA pull-up to 3V3 |
| R12 | 1 | Resistor | 4.7kΩ | 0603 | I2C SCL pull-up to 3V3 |

**PCA9685 J6 Pin Header (6 pins):**

| Pin | Net | Notes |
|-----|-----|-------|
| 1 | +5V | Module VCC (logic supply) |
| 2 | GND | |
| 3 | I2C_SDA | Shared I2C bus with pull-up R11 |
| 4 | I2C_SCL | Shared I2C bus with pull-up R12 |
| 5 | +6V_SERVO | V+ rail for servo power (separate) |
| 6 | GND | Servo power return |

**I2C Address:** 0x40 (default, all address pins to GND on module)
**Servo power:** Module has separate V+ screw terminal. Connect to 6V_SERVO rail, NOT logic VCC.

**I2C Pull-up Calculation (400kHz Fast Mode):**
```
R_pull-up = (VCC - VOL_max) / I_sink
Target: rise time t_r < 300ns with bus capacitance ~100pF
R = t_r / (0.8473 × C_bus) = 300ns / (0.8473 × 100pF) ≈ 3.5kΩ minimum
4.7kΩ chosen → adequate margin, lower power than 2.2kΩ ✅
```

