| R16 | 1 | Resistor | 1kΩ | 0603 | Enc2 ChB RC filter series R |
| C7 | 1 | Capacitor | 10nF ceramic | 0603 | Enc1 ChA RC filter cap |
| C8 | 1 | Capacitor | 10nF ceramic | 0603 | Enc1 ChB RC filter cap |
| C9 | 1 | Capacitor | 10nF ceramic | 0603 | Enc2 ChA RC filter cap |
| C10 | 1 | Capacitor | 10nF ceramic | 0603 | Enc2 ChB RC filter cap |

**Encoder pin-out (each J7, J8):**

| Pin | Net | Notes |
|-----|-----|-------|
| 1 | +3V3 | Encoder VCC — 3.3V so output signals are GPIO-safe |
| 2 | GND | |
| 3 | ENCx_A | Channel A → RC filter → ESP32 GPIO |
| 4 | ENCx_B | Channel B → RC filter → ESP32 GPIO |

**RC Filter Cut-off Frequency:** f_c = 1/(2π×1kΩ×10nF) = **15.9kHz**
At 330 RPM motor max: pulse rate ≈ 330/60 × PPR (encoder resolution). Filter passes signal, rejects EMI spikes.

> IMPORTANT: Encoders MUST be powered from **3V3**, not 5V. If powered from 5V, the Hall effect output signals would be 5V and would exceed ESP32 GPIO maximum of 3.3V — permanent damage risk.

