**J9 RPi Power (GPIO method — bypasses USB-C PD requirement):**

| Pin | Net | Notes |
|-----|-----|-------|
| 1 | +5V | → RPi GPIO Pin 2 or Pin 4 |
| 2 | GND | → RPi GPIO Pin 6 |

> IMPORTANT: Raspberry Pi 5 can be powered via GPIO pins 2/4 (5V) + pin 6 (GND), bypassing the USB-C port entirely. This is the "Option A" selected: direct 5V delivery without need for USB-C PD negotiation. Max safe current: ~5A via GPIO pins.

**J10 RPi UART:**

| Pin | Net | Notes |
|-----|-----|-------|
| 1 | GND | Common ground |
| 2 | +3V3 | Optional reference |
| 3 | RPi_TX → ESP32_RX | RPi TXD → GPIO35 on ESP32 (INPUT ONLY) |
| 4 | ESP32_TX → RPi_RX | ESP32 TXD → RPi RXD |

> RPi GPIO is 3.3V logic. ESP32 GPIO is 3.3V. No level shifting needed. ✅

