## 7. Design Rules Checklist

- [ ] No trace under Q1 SO-8 thermal pad — use via-stitched copper pour to GND
- [ ] AMS1117 output cap must be ≥10µF (datasheet requirement for stability)
- [ ] I2C pull-ups tied to 3V3 (not 5V) — PCA9685 and ESP32 share 3.3V I2C
- [ ] Encoder VCC = 3V3 ONLY — confirmed to avoid 5V on GPIO inputs
- [ ] ENA/ENB (GPIO25/26) have 10kΩ pull-down to GND — confirmed (R19, R20)
- [ ] GPIO12 — if connected, add 10kΩ pull-down to GND (flash voltage strapping pin)
- [ ] L298N ENA/ENB jumpers REMOVED before connecting J11
- [ ] MPU-6500 FSYNC tied to GND via J5 pin 8
- [ ] Decoupling caps placed within 2mm of IC power pins
- [ ] 3V3 TVS diode D1 (SMAJ3.3A) for transient protection
- [ ] All ground returns star-routed to battery negative — no ground loops
- [ ] GND plane (In1.Cu) unbroken — no splits, no routing through it
- [ ] XL4016 output verified at correct voltage BEFORE connecting to PCB
- [ ] Test points on: VBAT, +5V, +3V3, +6V_SERVO, GND, SPI_CS, IMU_INT

